@startuml
title Arquitectura de Threads — Servidor

class Server {
  - listener: Socket
  - input_queue: Queue<PlayerCommand>
  - monitor: ClientListMonitor
  - acceptor: Acceptor
  - game_loop: GameLoop
  + run()
  - stop()
}

class Acceptor extends Thread {
  - listener: Socket&
  - input_queue: Queue<PlayerCommand>&
  - monitor: ClientListMonitor&
  + run()
  + stop()
}

class GameLoop extends Thread {
  - game: Game
  - input_queue: Queue<PlayerCommand>&
  - monitor: ClientListMonitor&
  + run()
  - dispatch(result: CommandResult, origin: optional<uint16_t>)
}

class ClientListMonitor {
  - mtx: mutex
  - clients: map<uint16_t, unique_ptr<ClientHandler>>
  - next_id: uint16_t
  + add(skt: Socket&&, input_queue: Queue<PlayerCommand>&): uint16_t
  + push_event(player_id: uint16_t, event: ServerEvent)
  + broadcast(event: ServerEvent)
  + clean_dead(): vector<uint16_t>
  + stop_all()
}
note right of ClientListMonitor
  Único punto de sincronización
  (mutex) entre Acceptor y GameLoop:
  todos los ClientHandler viven acá.
end note

class ClientHandler {
  - player_id: uint16_t
  - protocol: ServerProtocol
  - output_queue: Queue<ServerEvent>
  - sender: Sender
  - receiver: Receiver
  + start()
  + push_event(ev: ServerEvent)
  + stop()
  + join()
  + is_alive(): bool
}

class Sender extends Thread {
  - output_queue: Queue<ServerEvent>&
  - protocol: ServerProtocol&
  + run()
}

class Receiver extends Thread {
  - input_queue: Queue<PlayerCommand>&
  - protocol: ServerProtocol&
  + run()
}

class ServerProtocol {
  + send_event(ev: ServerEvent)
  + recv_command(): ClientCommand
  + shutdown_from_other_thread()
}

class Queue<T> {
  + push(item: T)
  + pop(): T
  + try_pop(item: T&): bool
  + try_push(item: T): bool
  + close()
}

Server *-- Acceptor : <<dueño>>
Server *-- GameLoop : <<dueño>>
Server *-- ClientListMonitor : <<dueño>>
Acceptor --> ClientListMonitor : monitor.add()\n<<crea ClientHandler>>
GameLoop --> ClientListMonitor : push_event() / broadcast()\n<<dispatch de CommandResult>>
GameLoop --> ClientListMonitor : clean_dead()\n<<destraba sockets muertos>>
ClientListMonitor o-- ClientHandler : <<contiene, protegido por mtx>>
ClientHandler *-- Sender
ClientHandler *-- Receiver
GameLoop --> Queue: try_pop() comandos en loop\n<<no bloqueante, tick fijo>>\n(input_queue global)
Receiver --> Queue: push() comandos (input_queue global)
ClientHandler *-- "out" Queue: eventos privados\n(una Queue<ServerEvent> por cliente)
Sender --> ServerProtocol
Receiver --> ServerProtocol
note right of Queue
  Cola MPMC bloqueante
  Thread-safe
end note
@enduml